lParserAPIsTest doesn't really test anything, so maybe I should leave it as a placeholder or remove it altogether. I’m looking to maintain a one-to-one mapping between dynamic report classes and generated test class files, but I don’t want a generic placeholder. I need to ensure that the provider class extends DocumentBuilderFactory. Also, I'll use AssertJ for assertions.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Implementing SecuritySupportTest**\\n\\nI'm working on the SecuritySupportTest class that extends DocumentBuilderFactory. It has a static final FACTORY_ID and a attributes map to hold settings. I’m writing tests to ensure the factory discovery loads the provider correctly. In one test, I’m clearing properties and adjusting the context class loader to check if the factory instance is of the SecuritySupportTest class. In another test, I need to verify loading from system resources when there’s no context class loader. I wonder, what happens if the JDK factory relies on a system property?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Bm8qv1bWd08SQDvKXRVIFF4F|fc_0daefcc6e951c0ee0169f1493f41bc8193998d1f3fc06e2aa7", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src -path '*/src/test/resources/META-INF/services/*' | head -20 -print && find tests/src -path '*/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json' | head -10 -print -exec head -80 {} \\;", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 799, "output": 1078, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33621, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777420593286, "responseId": "resp_0daefcc6e951c0ee0169f14931c1708193ba6a3c7c2f4b49cb"}}
